---
title: Spiced Moroccan Lentil and Chickpea Soup
description: They say you can lead a camel to water but you can’t make him drink. We’re pretty sure if you led him to this steaming bowl of Moroccan soup, you wouldn’t have a problem! This recipe is inspired by Head Chef Patrick’s recent trip to the Atlas Mountains where he spent time with the nomadic Berbers. Check out the video of his adventure on our blog!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/55488fb76ced6e14498b4568.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/55488fb76ced6e14498b4568.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/spiced-moroccan-lentil-and-chickpea-soup-55488fb76ced6e14498b4568
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 603 kcal
  fat: 11 g
  saturated fat: 4 g
  carbohydrates: 113 g
  protein: 31 g
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: North African
---

Boil 500ml of water in a #pot{}. Peel the @red onion{1}, cut in half lengthways
through the root and thinly slice. Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1%400g can}.
Roughly chop the @coriander{3%sprigs} separating the stalks and the leaves.

Heat @oil{1%tbsp} in a pan on medium-low heat and add the @ground cumin{2%tsp},
@ground cloves{1/4%tsp} and @smoked paprika{1%tsp}. After ~{1%minute}, add the
onions and cook for ~{5%minutes} until soft. Add the chopped coriander stalks
for ~{1%minute}. Season with @salt{1/4%tsp}.

Add the @chopped tomatoes{1%400g can} and the @tomato puree{1%tbsp}. Add the 500ml
of water together with the @vegetable stock pot{1}.

Rinse the @red split lentils{1/2%cup} thoroughly under running water for
~{1%minute}. Add them to the soup and bubble away for ~{10%minutes}.

Add the chickpeas and half the coriander leaves and cook for another
~{10%minutes}.

Once the soup has thickened up, taste for seasoning and add @salt{} if needed.

> Tip: Patrick adds a bit of Tabasco to his to spice things up!

Meanwhile, toast the @pitta bread{2}.

Serve the soup into bowls with fresh coriander on top. Dollop on some
@Greek style natural yoghurt{2%tbsp} and serve.